BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Community
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by Daniel Shaw\, this session offers a quiet space to se
 ttle the nervous system and be together without pressure to analyze or resp
 ond to events. We will begin with simple breath awareness\, followed by gen
 tle floor-based movement practiced mostly on the back\, restorative poses\,
  and a guided Progressive Muscle Relaxation. The hour will close with a bri
 ef loving-kindness meditation. Everything is invitational—participants may 
 rest\, modify\, or simply be present. No prior yoga or meditation experienc
 e is needed\, and all mats\, blankets\, and props will be provided. The int
 ention is modest: one hour where breath can soften\, muscles can unclench\,
  and the community can share silence without needing to explain\, perform\,
  or fix anything.\n\nThis event is part of the Day of Reflection and Commun
 ity Action\, featuring workshops and activities led by students\, faculty\,
  staff\, and alumni. The day is designed to create space for learning\, fee
 ling\, dialogue\, and connection. \n\nBrowse other events that are a part o
 f the Day of Reflection and Community Action here.
DTEND:20260217T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260217T200000Z
GEO:45.481735;-122.633397
LOCATION:Sports Center\, Upper Fitness Studio
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Mindful Movement & Rest as Resistance 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52083773361684
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/mindful-movement-rest-as-resistance
