CATEGORIES:Community
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by Mara McKenzie-Levine\, participants will examine the 
 approaches and consequences of federal agencies' reactions to protests from
  2020-2026 from both a sociological and on-the-ground perspective. We will 
 discuss the exact methods of political repression that they engage in and w
 hat the impacts of that are on both a personal and movement-level. The clas
 s will draw on Mara's knowledge as a sociology student writing a thesis on 
 this topic and their personal experiences being arrested and detained by DH
 S. \n\nThis event is part of the Day of Reflection and Community Action\, f
 eaturing workshops and activities led by students\, faculty\, staff\, and a
 lumni. The day is designed to create space for learning\, feeling\, dialogu
 e\, and connection. \n\nBrowse other events that are a part of the Day of R
 eflection and Community Action here.
