BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:A Probabilistic Invitation to Ergodic Theory - \nErgodic theory
  is the study of deterministic dynamical systems with random initial data. 
  In this talk\, I'll present a biased selection of definitions\, theorems\,
  and typical research questions in ergodic theory.  Along the way\, I'll il
 lustrate each new concept and result in the simplest possible case: the ite
 rated transposition of two distinct elements.  My goal is to explain why (i
 ) dynamical systems ``in equilibrium'' aren't ``static'' and (ii) Poincaré'
 s recurrence theorem and Birkhoff's ergodic theorem each provide a bridge b
 etween equilibrium and non-equilibrium dynamics.  After establishing these 
 general principles\, I'll present work in progress with Robert Chang (New C
 ollege of Florida) on Liouville-Arnold integrability of deterministic Hamil
 tonian PDEs with Gaussian random initial data.
DTEND:20260220T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260219T234000Z
