 -reed-college
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:The Chemistry Department invites you to join us for our weekly 
 seminar series! This week\, we welcome Dr. Peter Alaimo from Seattle Univer
 sity.\n\nPeter J. Alaimo\n\n4:30 pm\n\nBiology 19\n\nHow Making Molecules E
 nables Diverse Scientific Discovery\n\nAbstract: Organic chemistry can some
 times seem like an endless list of reactions to know. While thinking about 
 synthesis can strike fear in the minds of the novice\, it is also a way to 
 make organic chemistry useful to a diverse array of fields. In this seminar
 \, I will tell you 5 stories about how my lab has made molecules that were 
 important to scientists in other fields\, to answer key questions those sci
 entists had. The stories will come from collaborations with neuroscientists
 \, microbiologists\, materials scientists\, environmental scientists\, and 
 agricultural chemists at research universities across the US and Europe.
DTEND:20260220T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260220T003000Z
GEO:45.480779;-122.627995
LOCATION:Biology\, 19
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Chemistry Seminar: Peter J. Alaimo
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52144365301494
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/chemistry-seminar-speaker
END:VEVENT
