BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Informational Session
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in creating art for social good? Love to doo
 dle but unsure how it could factor into a career? Join CLBR and Shay Mirk\,
  the founder of Crucial Comix for a chat about what they publish\, how they
  publish\, and why they publish! Shay and Audra\, Crucial's editor\, will b
 e here to answer questions about Crucial Comix and their professional journ
 eys within art\, authorship\, and graphic journalism. Light snacks and drin
 ks provided. Read more about Crucial Comix's mission below:\n\nComics have 
 the power to shape how we understand both ourselves and the world. In short
 \, comics are crucial.\n\nCrucial Comix is an artist-centered\, narrative-n
 onfiction press that is rooted in collaboration\, community-building\, and 
 mutual enthusiasm. Our goal is to make comics-creation accessible to a new 
 era of artists. We work to expand the reach of independent cartoonists\, bu
 ild a mutually supportive comics community around the world\, and to empowe
 r people of all backgrounds with the skills to powerfully write\, draw\, an
 d share their own stories. Crucial Comix is helping to grow an entire ecosy
 stem of comics that document our ever-changing world. While most publishers
  are driven by advertising\, algorithms\, and increasingly dire political p
 ressures\, Crucial looks for complicated\, boundary-pushing comics that bui
 ld empathy\, offer new perspectives\, and help both artists and readers fee
 l more connected to the world.
DTEND:20260226T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260226T000000Z
GEO:45.479343;-122.633461
LOCATION:Prexy\, Prexy Living Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Sketches and Social Justice: A Crucial Conversation with Crucial Co
 mix
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52092640458060
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/sketches-and-social-justice-a-crucial-con
 versation-with-crucial-comix
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Global and Public Health Research Pathways\n\nIn this talk\, I 
 will share my path into global and public health research and introduce imp
 lementation science-an approach focused on understanding how evidence-based
  health\ninterventions actually work in realworld settings. The talk is org
 anized in three parts. (1) I will describe my professional background and t
 raining trajectory\; (2) I will give a brief overview of implementation sci
 ence\; (3) I will present findings from my ongoing mixed-methods research o
 n HIV care models in China. The talk willemphasize how these approaches can
  be applied to diverse public health questions and how students can engage 
 in global health and health systems research.\n\nPizza will be served!
DTEND:20260226T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260226T001000Z
GEO:45.480644;-122.627381
LOCATION:Psychology\, 103
SEQUENCE:0
