BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Community
DESCRIPTION:REED UNION!\n\nOn Friday\, February 27\, there will be a Reed U
 nion to discuss Free Speech\, building off of our discussion of the Honor P
 rinciple from the fall. The Union will be held in the Kaul auditorium from 
 3:15 - 5:00 PM. All community members are encouraged to attend. There will 
 be beverages and snacks provided. Please join us!\n\nReed College has a lon
 g-standing tradition of hosting campus-wide conversations to discuss topics
  relevant to the Reed community\, which we call Reed Unions. The first Reed
  Union was held in 1947 (there is a very interesting history of the Reed Un
 ion on the Reed website)\, but there have been no recent Reed Unions since 
 COVID until September 26\, 2025. With over 120 attendees\, Reedies came tog
 ether as a community to discuss the Honor Principle and its meaning today. 
 Students\, Staff\, Faculty\, and Alumni all had chances to share their opin
 ions on the Honor Principle and engage in community dialogue.
DTEND:20260228T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260227T231500Z
GEO:45.481263;-122.633328
LOCATION:Kaul Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Reed Union Dialogue: Free Speech
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52128046195317
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/reed-union-dialogue-free-speech
END:VEVENT
