BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture,Student,Social
DESCRIPTION:Join the Reed Zine + Arts Program in hosting artist talks by He
 len Oji (NYC) and Yumi Sakugawa\, moderated by Ann "A'misa" Matsushima Chiu
 .\n\nReserve your spot today as seats are limited in Vollum Lounge. \n\nAbo
 ut the Speakers:\n\nHelen Oji interweaves her Japanese heritage with Americ
 an and European visual traditions\, exploring gesture\, paint\, color\, and
  form. In 1990\, she was one of thirteen founding members of GODZILLA: Asia
 n American Art Network. The Smithsonian American Art Museum has recently ac
 quired four of her prints\, and the Smithsonian Institution libraries and A
 rchives hold her art papers\, documenting more than fifty years of artistic
  practice. Oji’s work is held in major public collections\, including the M
 useum of Modern Art\, the Brooklyn Museum\, the High Museum of Art\, and th
 e Library of Congress. She lives and works in New York City.\n\nYumi Sakuga
 wa is a second-generation Japanese-Okinawan-American interdisciplinary arti
 st based in Los Angeles and the author of several books including Your Illu
 strated Guide To Becoming One With The Universe and There Is No Right Way t
 o Meditate. Her comics have appeared in The New Yorker\, Bitch\, The Rumpus
 \, and other publications. A graduate from the fine art program of Universi
 ty of California\, Los Angeles\, she currently lives in Los Angeles.\n\nAnn
  "A'misa" Matsushima Chiu is a fourth-generation Japanese American libraria
 n and zinester\, who is currently the Social Sciences and Zine Librarian at
  Reed College. A'misa\, alongside Chloe Van Stralendorff\, co-organizes the
  Reed Zine Fest\, alongside student zine czars Aida Tada and Andreanna Gude
 . She is also a co-organizer of the Azn Zine Fest\, who received the 2026 P
 recipice Grant from the Portland Institute of Contemporary Arts. \n\nThis e
 vent is being co-hosted by the Azn Zine Fest\, which is being held the foll
 owing day\, 2/28\, at Fubonn from 12-5pm.
DTEND:20260228T033000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260228T020000Z
GEO:45.480964;-122.630146
LOCATION:Vollum College Center\, Vollum Lounge
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Asian American Women Artist Talk with Helen Oji and Yumi Sakugawa
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51960558476220
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/asian-american-women-artist-talk-with-hel
 en-oji-and-yumi-sakugawa
END:VEVENT
