URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/math-statistics-colloquium-blair-davey-mo
 ntana-state-university
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:The Chemistry Department invites you to join us for our weekly 
 seminar series! This week\, we welcome Dr. Chris Vanderwal\, Professor of C
 hemistry at UC Irvine.\n\nDr. Chris Vanderwal\n\n4:30 pm\n\nBiology 19\n\n 
 \n\nA General Platform of the Synthesis of Antimalarial Isocyanoterpenes\n\
 nAbstract: The combination of compelling structures and attractive biologic
 al activities motivates our group to engage in the total synthesis of compl
 ex\, polycyclic natural products. In this lecture\, I will discuss our work
  in the area of antimalarial isocyanoterpenes\, focusing on our efforts to 
 develop a general strategy to access several structurally different members
  of the family\, with the goal of driving collaborative studies into their 
 mechanism of action. In the course of this work\, numerous examples of fasc
 inating and unusual reactivity have been uncovered\, which might have impli
 cations beyond the specific case at hand.
DTEND:20260306T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260306T003000Z
