BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performing Arts
DESCRIPTION:Ticketing is by day\, not by show. Your ticket gets you entry t
 o BOTH shows each evening. Purchase tickets here.\n\nThursday\, March 5th \
 nThe Maids @ 7:30pm\nSiren Songs @ 9:15pm\n\nFriday\, March 6th \nSiren Son
 gs @ 7:30pm\nThe Maids @ 8:45pm\n\nSaturday\, March 7th \nThe Maids @ 7:30p
 m\nSiren Songs @ 9:15pm\n \n\nSiren Songs by Lindsay Partain. A performance
  thesis directed by Lily Olcott\n\nSet in “a tree house on the edge of the 
 world\,” Siren Songs blends horror\, tragedy\, and hints of the supernatura
 l. In a remote lighthouse haunted by ghosts and myths\, two lighthouse keep
 ers wrestle with sanity and mortality as they struggle to keep the light bu
 rning amidst extreme storms.\n\nThis show contains physical violence\, illn
 ess\, death\, extreme isolation\, hallucinations\, and brief suicidal ideat
 ion.\n\n \n\nThe Maids by Jean Genet. A performance thesis directed by Dant
 e Tirado Morales\n\nJean Genet's The Maids enacts an evening in the life of
  two maids in a 1940s Parisian apartment as they race against time to play-
 act the muder of their mistress. As their performance unfurls\, both maids 
 reckon with the sense of bone-deep hopelessness and comical absurdity of tr
 ying to exist under a nexus of capitalism and gendered scripts as the stori
 es they tell to keep themselves grounded begin to crumble.\n\nThis show con
 tains physical and verbal abuse and suicide.
DTEND:20260307T043000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260307T033000Z
