BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Alumni
DESCRIPTION:Let’s brunch at Agate Alley Bistro\, then hang out and learn to
 gether at the Jordan Schnitzer Museum of Art on University of Oregon’s camp
 us!\n\nWe will meet at Agate Alley Bistro at 10am to hang out and enjoy bru
 nch on a private heated patio ahead of our museum visit. It is a fifteen mi
 nute\, half mile walk from the bistro to the museum. You will be responsibl
 e for your own food spending\, but the museum admission and tour are on Ree
 d!\n\nJSMA's group tours are a treat and actively engage participants in vi
 sual thinking strategies to dive deeper into the art experience. We will pl
 an to be at the museum by 12:45pm and then begin our tour at 1pm. This will
  all leave plenty of time for independent exploration before the museum clo
 ses at 5pm.\n\nHere’s a bit about the current exhibition from the museum’s 
 website:\nLove\, Desire\, and Sorrow examines the notions of house\, home\,
  and the body to explore the factors and social entities that define them. 
 [The exhibition] foregrounds the notion of home\, broadly defined\, to pond
 er the economic\, social\, cultural\, and political structures\, policies\,
  and events that shape our current existence. Artists in the exhibition inv
 estigate colonialism\, slavery\, and the diaspora\, evoking quilts or repre
 senting subjects under duress in situations where the home and body exist i
 n a state of threat. [...] In sculptures\, prints and textiles\, artworks i
 n the exhibition contest normative representations of home and body as the 
 artists consider notions of belonging\, justice\, and healing.\nParking is 
 free in the parking lot near to the museum on 14th & Alder (more accessibil
 ity information here).\n\nWe hope to see you then!\n\nSincerely\,\nAmanda ‘
 91 and Ashley ‘07\n\n*Please let us know you're coming\, by February 26\, u
 sing the following Google Form.
DTEND:20260307T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
