BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a night of readings in Eliot Chapel with visiting w
 riters Hannah Baer and David Velasco. A Q+A will follow and refreshments wi
 ll be served. Free and open to the public.\n\n \n\nDavid Velasco is a write
 r based in New York. He is the recipient of a Cultural Freedom Award from t
 he Lannan Foundation (2024) and fellowships from the MacDowell Colony and D
 enniston Hill (2025). From 2005 to 2023 he was an editor at Artforum and wa
 s editor in chief for the last six of those years. His early days were comm
 itted to elevating the status of dance and performance in Artforum’s pages\
 , and in 2016 he was the creator of and series editor for “Modern Dance\,” 
 published by the Museum of Modern Art. Most recently\, he has written on th
 e murder of his friend Brent Sikkema (“The Good Pervert\,” Harper’s\, Oct 2
 025) and the Palestinian exception in speech (“How Gaza Broke the Art World
 \,” Equator\, Dec 2025). He is currently working on a memoir about the conv
 ergence of personal and political atrocity. \n\n \n\nhannah baer is a write
 r and licensed clinical psychologist based in New York. She is the author o
 f the memoir trans girl suicide museum and the nonfiction book The Life of 
 the Party forthcoming in 2027. She is a psychoanalytic candidate and a cont
 ributing editor to Parapraxis.
DTEND:20260308T033000Z
