BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Garbled Circuits: What they are and what they are good for -\nI
 n this talk I will describe Garbled Circuits\, a technique for doing secure
  multiparty computation\, in which two parties would like to compute some f
 unction on their private inputs without revealing anything about their inpu
 ts besides what can be learned from the function output. I will cover the b
 asic Garbled Circuit construction alongside several optimizations\, in a wa
 y that hopefully gets across the core ideas of the approach to those with n
 o prior knowledge in the area. I will end with some novel uses of Garbled C
 ircuits that we are exploring at Galois.
DTEND:20260310T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260310T224000Z
