BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Braids and Combinatorics -\nCombinatorics is\, in principle\, t
 he subject devoted to counting certain kinds of mathematical objects.  Seve
 ral objects appear regularly in this story: subsets\, partitions\, permutat
 ions\, and the like.  I’ll begin with an introduction to these objects and 
 how combinatorialists count them.  With that in hand\, I’ll discuss “braide
 d” analogues of these constructions — these have a much more geometric flav
 or\, but still retain some of the original combinatorial aspects.  This all
 ows us to upgrade the familiar notions of finite sets and functions between
  them to a world of braided sets and functions.
DTEND:20260312T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260312T224000Z
GEO:45.480972;-122.630792
LOCATION:Eliot Hall\, 314
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Math & Statistics Colloquium: Craig Westerland\, University of Minn
 esota
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51738880485255
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/math-statistics-colloquium-craig-westerla
 nd-university-of-minnesota
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:The Chemistry Department invites you to join us for our weekly 
 seminar series! This week\, we welcome Alison Frontier\, Professor of Chemi
 stry\, University of Rochester.\n\nDr. Alison Frontier\n\n4:30 pm\n\nBiolog
 y 19\n\nNavigational Surprises in Organic Synthesis\n\nAbstract: During res
 earch in the organic chemistry laboratory\, we sometimes find that experime
 nts give us unexpected results.  When assembling complex molecules in the l
 aboratory\, sometimes the things we learn accidentally are frustrating and 
 disappointing\, but sometimes they are the tip of an interesting iceberg.  
 Unexpected results can be important clues that help us recalibrate our synt
 hetic strategy\, based on a new understanding of how our molecules behave. 
  In some cases\, these surprise results help us discover novel reaction che
 mistry as well.
DTEND:20260313T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021911Z
DTSTART:20260312T233000Z
GEO:45.480779;-122.627995
LOCATION:Biology\, 19
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Chemistry Seminar: Dr. Alison Frontier
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52144407500815
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/chemistry-seminar-dr-alison-frontier
