BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:The year is 2026\, and the Trump administration violates the Co
 nstitution so regularly that it scarcely makes the news anymore. Masked par
 amilitary goons invade our cities\, where they abduct\, imprison\, and murd
 er people with apparent impunity. Warehouse concentration camps run by priv
 ate prison companies mushroom into communities across the country. America'
 s support of Israel's atrocities in Gaza continues\, and we have once again
  destabilized the Middle East with an unprovoked war that promises to kill 
 thousands. It is very easy to become overwhelmed at times like this. What c
 an any of us do to stop this juggernaut? What meaningful actions can we tak
 e? This talk will explore what we can do\, as individuals and as a collecti
 ve\, to fight back and keep our neighbors safe\, and why we have reason to 
 hope for a brighter\, better future.\n\nLaura Jedeed ('19) is a freelance j
 ournalist at firewalledmedia.com who recently exposed ICE's lax hiring prac
 tices for Slate. Her work has also appeared in publications like Rolling St
 one\, Politico\, and Slate. Laura's Reed thesis centered around a 1.5-year 
 ethnography of Patriot Prayer\, a far-right group affiliated with the Proud
  Boys\, and her work primarily focuses on American conservatism. When not w
 riting or arguing online\, you can find her taking pictures of graffiti and
  enjoying New York City's EDM scene.\n\nFree and open to the public.
DTEND:20260318T030000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260318T020000Z
GEO:45.480964;-122.630146
LOCATION:Vollum College Center\, Lecture Hall
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:What Is To Be Done? How to Take Action in Horrifying Times
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52259387386753
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/what-is-to-be-done-how-to-take-action-in-
 horrifying-times
END:VEVENT
