BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:Graphs Viewed Through Commutative Algebra -\nEdge ideals of gra
 phs were introduced by Rafael Villarreal in the 1990s and binomial edge ide
 als were introduced by Herzog\, Hibi\, Hreinsdottir\, Kahle and Rauh and in
 dependently by Ohtani\, in 2010\, all to study the graph-theoretic properti
 es through commutative algebra.  The specific ideal-theoretic properties th
 at play a role are various matching numbers\, connectivity\, the Castelnuov
 o-Mumford regularity\,arithmetical rank\, associated primes of powers of id
 eals\, and more. This talk will be a survey of the area.
DTEND:20260319T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260319T224000Z
GEO:45.480972;-122.630792
LOCATION:Eliot Hall\, 314
