BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special screening of Tarajal: Desmontando la impu
 nidad en la frontera sur (Tarajal:A European Phantasmagoria) a documentary 
 directed by Xavier Artigas\, Xapo Ortega\, and Marc Serra\, 2015. The film 
 examines the massacre of 15 immigrants attempting to swim to the Tarrajal B
 each in Ceuta\, Spain and "articulates a rigorous investigation through vid
 eos recorded by witnesses\, media footage\, legal analysis and interviews w
 ith lawyers\, activists and victims' relatives. Its strength lies in its ca
 pacity to dismantle the Spanish government's official narrative and to expo
 se systematic practices of racist violence and the lack of institutional ac
 countability" (https://www.xavierartigas.cat/en/cinema/tarjal-a-spanish-pha
 ntasmagoria/)\nThe documentary will be the focus of a discussion led by Món
 ica López Lerma\, April 8\, 4:10-5:30 in Kaul Lounge\, as part of the "Lang
 uages of Truth Series" organized by the Program in Comparative Literature.
DTEND:20260408T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260408T023000Z
GEO:45.480644;-122.627381
LOCATION:Psychology\, 105
SEQUENCE:0
