BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshop/Training
DESCRIPTION:Languages of Truth is a seminar series that examines how the co
 ncept of truth persists within literary\, aesthetic\, and historical discou
 rses\, despite sustained arguments that have exposed it as mediated\, conti
 ngent\, and rhetorically framed. We will ask why appeals to a true/false di
 stinctions remain indispensable—and why they have become especially volatil
 e today\, amid claims of “post-truth\,” strategic disinformation\, and the 
 overt monetization of persuasion. Sponsored by the Comparative Literature P
 rogram.\n\nPlease note: 3/4 event will be held in Trillium Multi-Purpose ro
 om\, not Gray Lounge.
DTEND:20260409T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260408T231000Z
GEO:45.481263;-122.633328
LOCATION:Kaul Auditorium\, Gray Lounge
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Languages of Truth
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51837000762744
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/languages-of-truth
END:VEVENT
