BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture
DESCRIPTION:This July marks the 250th anniversary of the Declaration of Ind
 ependence\, the pinnacle of a longer commemoration of the American Revoluti
 on's semiquincentennial. This panel of Reed faculty and visiting scholars w
 ill use this landmark anniversary as an occasion to reflect on the state of
  the United States today--and how we got here. Topics likely to be consider
 ed include culture wars\, American empire\, birthright citizenship\, state-
 federal relations\, and whatever members of the audience wish to bring up. 
 Come join us as we grapple with the past\, present\, and future of the U.S.
  in advance of its 250th birthday.\n\n \n\nSponsored by the American Studie
 s Program.
DTEND:20260415T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260415T000000Z
GEO:45.480972;-122.630792
LOCATION:Eliot Hall\, Chapel
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The United States of America: A 250th Anniversary Assessment
