BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lecture,Reception
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with eminent energy consulting expert Ro
 bert McCullough '72 on Tuesday\, April 14 at 6pm in Vollum Lecture Hall and
  Lounge.\n\n6–7 p.m. - Vollum Lecture Hall - What Causes Urban Wildfires: A
 pplying L.A.’s Lessons to Portland\nRobert will examine how laws\, economic
  incentives\, and institutional structures shape wildfire outcomes\, with a
  close look at the fragmented and siloed agencies that understood the risk 
 but couldn't coordinate an effective response. Wildfire has evolved from a 
 regional\, seasonal threat into a continental crisis\, as demonstrated by l
 ast year's $30-billion disaster in Los Angeles—a city with sophisticated pl
 ans and expert knowledge that still failed to act in time. Robert's work wi
 th the New York Times last January helped identify the ignition point of th
 e Eaton fire in Los Angeles. The presentation also brings the issue home to
  Portland\, where structural vulnerabilities similar to LA's put neighborho
 ods like Eastmoreland and Sellwood at serious risk.\n\n7:30–9 p.m. - Vollum
  Lounge - Reception\n\nJoin us for a reception after McCullough's presentat
 ion—light snacks and beverages will be served. Space is limited\, so please
  register today!\n\nREGISTER FOR THIS EVENT
DTEND:20260415T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260314T021912Z
DTSTART:20260415T010000Z
GEO:45.480964;-122.630146
LOCATION:Vollum College Center\, Vollum Lecture Hall and Lounge
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:What Causes Urban Wildfires: Applying L.A.’s Lessons to Portland - 
 by Robert McCullough ’72 - Lecture and Reception
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52198046592451
URL:https://events.reed.edu/event/robert-mccullough-wildfire-lecture-recept
 ion-april14-2026
END:VEVENT
